Model definition for Buzz.Activity. This class models an object which will be transmitted to or from the Lets you share updates, photos, videos, and more with your friends around the world service. To reduce the data transferred during service requests, you may remove members that contain data elements that your application does not need. responseHeaders

public com.google.api.client.http.HttpHeaders responseHeaders
The HTTP headers that were returned with the server response or null. This member will only be non-null if this object was the top level element of a response. For example, a request that returns a single Activity would include the responseHeaders, while a request which returns an array of Activity, would have a non-null responseHeader in the enclosing object only.
